b'' b' i am not a christian, however i suspect that all flavours of' b' christianity hold that (a) objective morality exists and (b) their' b' particular interpretation of scripture/revelation/tv is a goodly glimpse' b' of it. that they may all disagree about (b) says nothing about the truth' b' or falsehood of (a).' b'' b'actually, they generally claim that (b) their particular interpretation of' b'scripture/revelation *is* this objective morality. that there are two' b'conflicting versions of this objective morality does tell us something about' b'(a). it tells us at least one fake objective morality exists.' b'' b"the next logical step is to deduce that any given religion's objective" b'morality could be the fake one. so caveat emptor.' b'' b'' b'mathew' b'--' b'atheism: anti-virus software for the mind.' 